Having regard to Council Decision 78/688/EEC of 25 July 1978 setting up an Advisory Committee on the Training of Dental Practitioners (1), and in particular Articles 3 and 4 thereof,
Whereas under Article 3 of the said Decision the said Committee consists of three experts from each Member State and an alternate for each of those experts; whereas under Article 4 of the same Decision the term of office of those experts and alternates is three years;
Whereas, by its Decision of 25 July 1994 (2), the Council appointed the members and alternate members of the said Committee in respect of eleven Member States for the period from 25 July 1994 to 24 July 1997;
Whereas, by its Decision of 23 October 1995 (3), the Council appointed the members and alternate members of the said Committee in respect of three Member States for the period until 24 July 1997;
Whereas the Governments of fourteen Member States have each submitted a list of candidates for appointment, replacement or renewal of the term of office of those members and alternate members,
